# YouTube Cookies Template
# 
# To use this file:
# 1. Rename this file to "cookies.txt" (remove .example)
# 2. Export your browser cookies for youtube.com
# 3. Replace this content with your actual cookies
#
# How to export cookies:
# 
# Chrome:
# 1. Install "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" extension
# 2. Go to youtube.com and make sure you're logged in
# 3. Click the extension icon and download cookies.txt
# 4. Replace this file content with the downloaded content
#
# Firefox:
# 1. Install "cookies.txt" add-on
# 2. Go to youtube.com and make sure you're logged in  
# 3. Click the add-on icon and export cookies
# 4. Replace this file content with the exported content
#
# Manual method (Advanced):
# 1. Open browser Developer Tools (F12)
# 2. Go to Application/Storage tab
# 3. Find Cookies > https://www.youtube.com
# 4. Copy all cookies in Netscape format
#
# Example format (DO NOT USE THESE VALUES):
# # Netscape HTTP Cookie File
# .youtube.com	TRUE	/	FALSE	1234567890	VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE	example_value
# .youtube.com	TRUE	/	TRUE	1234567890	YSC	example_value
# .youtube.com	TRUE	/	FALSE	1234567890	PREF	example_value
#
# IMPORTANT: 
# - Keep your cookies.txt file private and secure
# - Never share your actual cookies with anyone
# - Cookies expire, so you may need to update them periodically